Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pour enough @oil{} into a deep #baking tray{} to cover the bottom and pop into the oven.

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil.

Peel and chop the @potatoes{700%grams} into 4cm chunks. Boil the potatoes for
~{7-8%minutes} or until the edges are soft.

When ready, drain in a #colander{} and sprinkle over some of the @plain flour{37.5%grams}.

> For portion sizes: 2p: 20g, 3p: 30g, 4p: 40g flour.

Shake to fluff up the potatoes, then carefully add them to the hot baking tray,
turning in the oil.

Season with @salt{}, sprinkle over the @dried rosemary{1%sachet}, then roast on the
top shelf until golden, ~{45-50%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Serve in a large #bowl{}.

== Roast Potatoes ==

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pour enough oil into a deep baking tray to cover the bottom and pop into the
oven.

Bring a large saucepan of water with salt to the boil.

Peel and chop the potatoes into 4cm chunks. Boil the potatoes for ~{7-8%minutes}
or until the edges are soft.

When ready, drain in a colander and sprinkle over some of the flour (20g per
portion).

Shake to fluff up the potatoes, then carefully add them to the hot baking tray,
turning in the oil.

Season with salt, sprinkle over the dried rosemary, then roast on the top shelf
until golden, ~{45-50%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Serve in a large bowl.

== Cauliflower Cheese ==

Cut the @cauliflower{1} into florets (like small trees), halving any large ones.

Pop the cauliflower onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread them out in a single layer.

Roast on the middle shelf until golden brown and tender, ~{18-20%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%grams}.

When the cauliflower has 5 mins roasting time remaining, melt the
@unsalted butter{20%grams} in a large saucepan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, stir in the @oil for the roux{1%tbsp} and some of the flour (20g per
portion). Cook until it forms a paste, ~{1-2%minutes} - you've made a roux!

Stir in the @water for the sauce{200%ml} a little at a time, followed by the
@vegetable stock paste{10%grams}.

Bring to the boil, then stir continuously and simmer until thickened,
~{1-2%minutes}.

Mix the @creme fraiche{150%grams} into the sauce, then remove from the heat.

Reserve a handful of the grated cheese.

Stir the roasted cauliflower and remaining cheese into your creamy sauce until
well combined and all the cheese has melted.

Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick. Taste and season with salt and
pepper if needed.

Transfer the cauliflower cheese to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}. Sprinkle
over the reserved cheese.

Place the cauliflower cheese onto a baking tray and add to the middle shelf of
your oven until golden and bubbling, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Serve in the dish.